    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing about 12 species and more than 50 recognized forms of graceful antelopes found on open plains and semideserts from Mongolia westward to the Atlantic coast of North Africa and throughout eastern and central tropical Africa. Three members of the genus Procapra are also commonly referred to as gazelles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
